if you won't indulge me you can fast forward I guess because it's a video.

13
00:00:48,660 --> 00:00:54,143
So Jackbox Games used to be called Jellyvision, and Jellyvision started out with a hit trivia

14
00:00:54,183 --> 00:01:00,306
game called You Don't Know Jack, which was released in 1995. As a side note, I started out

15
00:01:00,686 --> 00:01:06,569
at Jellyvision as an intern after getting this game for Hanukkah and writing a fancy fanboy letter

16
00:01:06,589 --> 00:01:12,712
to the company, and then, you know, I guess the rest is history. Been there 20-some years.

17
00:01:15,013 --> 00:01:20,274
So You Don't Know Jack was known as a trivia game where high culture and pop culture collided.

18
00:01:20,974 --> 00:01:26,856
So it had questions like this one. Which of the following household tasks can Superman not perform?

19
00:01:28,396 --> 00:01:32,857
