84
00:07:22,822 --> 00:07:27,865
As soon as I'm off this jet, we bought a zoo on Redbox.

85
00:07:28,246 --> 00:07:32,628
So every player would see that statement. They'd have to say if it's true or false.

86
00:07:33,409 --> 00:07:36,090
There was a leaderboard. Lots of fun.

87
00:07:38,199 --> 00:07:47,901
Unfortunately, it turns out movie theaters like using that time before movies start to sell ads and make money instead of paying game developers to entertain people.

88
00:07:49,382 --> 00:07:52,663
So this business never took off, but there was something compelling going on.

89
00:07:52,803 --> 00:07:55,364
Look at all these people happily playing on their phones.

90
00:07:56,784 --> 00:07:59,905
And so it felt like something we wanted to pursue even more.

91
00:08:01,740 --> 00:08:04,180
What came next was a new game called Fibbage.

92
00:08:05,701 --> 00:08:08,281
Fibbage is a bluffing game where you make up answers to

93
00:08:08,441 --> 00:08:12,662
obscure questions and try to tell the truth from the fiction.

94
00:08:13,743 --> 00:08:19,024
So for example, a Swedish man who works as a dishwasher receives disability

95
00:08:19,064 --> 00:08:22,505
benefits due to his unusual addiction to blank.

96
00:08:23,665 --> 00:08:27,686
All of the players type in an answer that they think could plausibly be correct.

97
00:08:28,266 --> 00:08:32,669
We show all of the player submitted answers along with the correct answer,

98
00:08:33,209 --> 00:08:35,431
which in this case is heavy metal music.

99
00:08:36,892 --> 00:08:39,433
And then everyone tries to guess which one is the correct answer.

100
00:08:41,335 --> 00:08:43,076
And Fibbage did well when it was released.

101
00:08:43,516 --> 00:08:47,198
It felt like we were onto something with this phones as controllers concept

102
00:08:47,679 --> 00:08:50,080
